section.summary
  h1 Delete a topic
  p Deleting a topic moves it to the <a href="discussion/Trash/id/1">trash</a>, where it can be recovered later if necessary. Once removed from the trash by an administrator, a topic is permanently deleted.
  p Announcements moved to the trash are removed from all discussions in which they appear.

if trash && trash.message
  section.notice.error
    p !{trash.message}

section.form.topic-trash
  form#topic-trash-form(action="topic/id/#{url.id}/action/trashForm" method="post" novalidate)
    .data
      input(name="forwardToUrl" type="hidden" value="#{form.forwardToUrl}")
      ul
        li.notify.checkbox
          input(id="notify" name="notify" type="checkbox" value="true" checked=form.notify)
          label(for="notify") Notify members following this topic
    .actions
      ul
        li.primary.report
          input(name="formAction" type="submit" value="Move this topic to the trash")
        li.secondary.cancel
          a(href="#{request.headers.referer}" title="Return to the page you came from.") Cancel and go back
